Gov. Atiku Bagudu of Kebbi State, says roads construction will be one of his top priorities in 2020. Bagudu made the commitment while inspecting ongoing township road projects in Kimba, Jandutsi and Alelu in Jega Local Government Area of the state. “In my policy thrust, construction of roads will be among my top priorities in 2020. “The aim is to transform urban and rural areas, as well as raise the economic wellbeing of the populace,’’ he said. The governor expressed satisfaction with the progress of work on the roads and urged the contractors to adhere to specifications of their contractual agreements. 6 girls die in Kebbi canoe mishap Commission issues Certificate of Return to elected LG… Court convicts 2 for obstructing FRSC personnel Police arrest 2 suspected kidnappers in Kebbi ALSO READ: APC chieftain commends FG for siting two higher institutions in Katsina State Bagudu reiterated his commitment to constructing more roads and providing social amenities across the 21 local government areas of the state. “We constructed roads in Ambursa, Zauro Town, Gwadangwaji Township, Bayan Kara and Bayan Tasha. “We are happy that we have put roads in Argungu Township, Zuru, Yauri and other local government areas in the state, and we are determined to do more,’’ he said. The governor also promised farmers in the area that the state government would open more access roads in rural areas to facilitate the movement of agricultural produce to desired destinations. NAN STAY STRONGER, LONGER AND SATISFY MADAM LIKE NEVER BEFORE WITH THIS NATURAL SUPPLEMENTS WITH NO SIDE EFFECTS. CLICK NOW. PREMATURE EJACULATION, SMALL SIZE FINALLY CURED NATURALLY IN 2 WEEKS FOR BIGGER, LONGER, HARDER SEXIER SEX WITH NEW MAN MACHINE